                Applied Machine Learning
                University of Massachusetts Boston
                Spring 2016

INTRODUCTION

    This repository contains the source code developed for Machine Learning
    course at University of Massachusetts Boston.
    It includes solutions to three assignments and one final exam.

BUILDING

    The package(s) needed for building source code on ubuntu trusty
    platform are listed below.

        - texlive-latex-base
        - texlive-latex-extra
        - texlive-science
        - r-base
        - pgf
        - ghostscript

    You will also need the `kernlab` package which could be installed
    using RStudio package management tool.

    Once you have all packages, all you need is `make` to run the
    R script, generate figures and produce the documents.

CONTRIBUTION

    Content of this repository is not subject to change. Bug reports
    however are appreciated.

